

The following are the most common types of parameters used in APIs:

• Path Parameters
• Query String Parameters
• Header Parameters
• Request Body Parameters

1:
Path Parameters

They are included in the URL path of an endpoint.

For example,

/users/{name}/posts/{id}


2:
Query String Parameters

Query parameters are widely used.

They start with a question mark (?).

There can be multiple query parameters in the endpoint which you can pass separately using the ampersand (&).

For example,

?name=john&id=1


3:
Header Parameters

They are included in the header of the request.

Generally, header parameters are used to pass sensitive data like API keys or credentials.


4:
Request Body Parameters

Generally, request body parameters are shipped in a JSON Object in POST, PUT, or PATCH requests.

The JSON object is included in the request body, so these parameters are called request body parameters.


